ng during that time, I can\'t just delete one occurence and leave the rest of the future occurences alone. I love the app otherwise but this problem is pushing me toward a different app.'),('Good app but need improvement'),('Its a nice app. Liked the design also. No option to copy paste same schedule to next day.'),('This is a good planner because it\'s easy to use and understand, but the widget consumes a lot of the phone\'s battery.'),('the app work just fine, it was my commitment that had problem '),('still trying'),('Got this, loved the free version. paid $3.99 for PRO and still don\'t have the ability (or can\'t figure out how and there are no instructions) to set different calendars on two widgets on my phone. I\'ll be happy to give you 5 stars if you send me a how-to. Also, it says there is time tracking. Does that mean I should be able to do a start-stop on something while I\'m doing an activity?'),('average features'),('It\'s pretty neat. I love the how everything pops out on the clock. Only thing is I tried scheduling things after 12 PM and it wouldn\'t pop up and I notice it only shows 12 hours at a time. If you buy the pro version it comes with the 24 hour feature, which I think is totally worth it. Seeing 24 hour option you can see everything from start to finish and not miss anything.'),('nice, but there seems to be no way to hide declined events? that makes it much less useful. Would give 5/5 otherwise'),('it just opens a-calender, so I\'m not sure why I need something between me and my regular calendar app.'),('Nice app! I just cannot work out what these random numbers are within the pieces of the pie... 35, 30, 7:35, 30, 8:35, 30, 8:35. it is clearly a countdown of some sort but bears no relevance to anything obvious. How can I remove these? UPDATE TO REPLY: Thank you, but I am seeing 7x this info around the pie and personally it serves little use. Can this function be disabled?'),('I uninstalled because the app was a little confusing. it has a grea